1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,670
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:09,009
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:09,092 --> 00:00:10,635
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,725
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:20,186
[Ibyang] Can I call you Mama Mary?

7
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,772
[Atoy] <i>And when did</i>
<i>you learn to skip class?</i>

8
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:23,982
<i>Looks like you even planned it.</i>

9
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:25,400
Where did you get this?

10
00:00:25,483 --> 00:00:26,818
I have a new friend.

11
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:28,695
Friend? Really?

12
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:30,488
[Janine] You even brought your neighbor

13
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:32,657
to pretend to be your father.

14
00:00:32,741 --> 00:00:34,325
And you believed my joke.

15
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:36,619
Doesn’t your dad joke with you too?

16
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:38,788
[student] <i>She doesn’t</i>
<i>really have a father.</i>

17
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:40,248
<i>Janine is just adopted.</i>

18
00:00:40,331 --> 00:00:41,916
[Roma] If the school calls me again,

19
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,252
I’ll return her to the orphanage!

20
00:00:44,335 --> 00:00:46,796
I’m willing to pay a lot of money.

21
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,298
Just give me the child.

22
00:00:48,381 --> 00:00:49,549
How much?

23
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:50,800
[Martina, in English] <i>Great news.</i>

24
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,218
<i>We’ve found your child.</i>

25
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:54,846
Are you sure that’s the child
you hid from me?

26
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:57,640
[Dmitri] It’s better to do
a DNA test first to be sure.

27
00:00:57,724 --> 00:01:00,310
[doctor] <i>Most probably, in five days</i>
<i>we’ll have the result.</i>

28
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:01,728
Will you also be the one to get

29
00:01:01,811 --> 00:01:03,104
the sample from the child?

30
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:05,774
Actually, I already sent
my lab tech with Martina

31
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:06,941
to make it faster.

32
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:09,944
All right, I’ll bring the child’s
DNA sample to the doctor.

33
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:11,154
[in English] Thank you.

34
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:11,988
‪PREVIOSLY

35
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,281
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

36
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:21,706
[Karla] You’re so slow, Sis Ame!

37
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:23,541
The barbecue stand might close.

38
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:25,084
[Tonet] Oh, wait!

39
00:01:25,168 --> 00:01:27,337
I forgot to list something! My God.

40
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:31,132
It’s because of Ibyang.
She couldn’t sleep.

41
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:34,677
She was too excited
about their field trip.

42
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:36,554
But that’s still tomorrow.

43
00:01:36,638 --> 00:01:38,056
By the way, Karla,

44
00:01:38,139 --> 00:01:40,225
why don’t you invite Gavin
to the theme park?

45
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:42,268
[Karla] Why would I do that?

46
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:44,312
He likes someone else, right?

47
00:01:44,395 --> 00:01:45,730
[light music playing]

48
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:47,732
He just likes her,
but they’re not together.

49
00:01:47,816 --> 00:01:49,567
It’s okay! You still have a chance.

50
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:53,822
Actually, that’s my dream.

51
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:56,699
For us to date at the theme park,

52
00:01:56,783 --> 00:02:00,370
and I’ll play mommy to Ibyang!

53
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:03,248
Then Atoy will play daddy.

54
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:06,543
This is really my chance with TTH.

55
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:09,337
Tonet, wake up!

56
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:13,216
Ibyang doesn’t want you as her mommy.

57
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:14,968
She wants Mama Mary!

58
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:17,804
Mama Mary?

59
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:20,974
How can I compete
with the mother of Jesus?

60
00:02:21,057 --> 00:02:22,517
[Ame] No!

61
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,894
That’s Ibyang’s new friend.

62
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:28,064
She calls her Mama Mary.

63
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:30,859
That’s who she wants
to pretend to be her mommy.

64
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:34,529
There! You lose, Sis Tonet!

65
00:02:34,612 --> 00:02:36,906
Your rival is Mama Mary’s face card.

66
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:40,076
- [scoffs]
- [Ame] I don’t get Ibyang.

67
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,995
Why does she keep picking random people

68
00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:43,538
to pretend to be her mommy?

69
00:02:43,621 --> 00:02:44,706
I’m right here.

70
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:47,041
I’m here, Ame.

71
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:52,130
It’s harder to believe if you’re
the mommy and Atoy’s the daddy.

72
00:02:52,213 --> 00:02:54,340
[smirks] Are you saying something?

73
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:55,800
- Are you saying something?
- [Tonet] Nothing, nothing.

74
00:02:55,884 --> 00:02:56,843
- [Ame] Ah, what?!
- Ouch…

75
00:02:56,926 --> 00:02:59,095
- Huh? Are you saying something?
- [Karla] You two are delusional.

76
00:02:59,762 --> 00:03:01,222
- Come on.
- This girl.

77
00:03:01,806 --> 00:03:03,349
Let’s go get some barbecue.

78
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:06,644
[music concludes]

79
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:10,982
I know…

80
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:14,986
you hear all my prayers.

81
00:03:15,069 --> 00:03:16,863
[melancholic music playing]

82
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:18,489
[in English] And I know…

83
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:22,785
that I was looking
for the wrong person before.

84
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,250
But now…

85
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:34,422
I know what’s more important than him.

86
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:38,509
[in English] Please.

87
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:43,431
Let me be with her.

88
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:50,563
[sobs] Let… me be with my daughter.

89
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:54,776
[optimistic music playing]

90
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:07,872
[music fades]

91
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:11,251
[suave theme music playing]

92
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:14,671
[motorcycle revving]

93
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:16,589
[sewing machine whirring]

94
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:17,548
[scratches]

95
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:19,133
[snipping]

96
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:22,470
[sewing machine whirring]

97
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:24,681
[gunshots blasting]

98
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:26,474
[gunshots blasting]

99
00:04:26,557 --> 00:04:28,142
[clicking]

100
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:29,560
[clicking]

101
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:31,854
[snipping]

102
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,147
[electronic blipping]

103
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:38,736
[music fades]

104
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:40,071
[birds chirping]

105
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,415
- Audrey, my child.
- [gentle music playing]

106
00:04:50,498 --> 00:04:53,084
[in English] Will you please
stop looking at your phone?

107
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,335
[in English] Let’s just eat.

108
00:04:55,503 --> 00:04:56,754
[in English] Ah, sorry, Dad.

109
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,048
I just can’t relax.

110
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:02,677
The DNA test results
are supposed to come out today.

111
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,220
Right, Auntie?

112
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:06,222
[in English] I know.

113
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:08,349
But you’re making us all tense.

114
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:11,311
We’re all waiting for those results.

115
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:13,521
[Martina, in English]
That’s right, Audrey.

116
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:15,398
Just relax.

117
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:16,983
[pensive music playing]

118
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:18,651
[phone blips]

119
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:21,946
The result is here.

120
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,990
[in English] Ah, what’s the result?

121
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:25,742
[music intensifies]

122
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,418
[in English] It’s a match, Dad.

123
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:36,961
[music fades]

124
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,671
She really is my missing child.

125
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:39,714
[chuckles]

126
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:41,049
[in English] Wow!

127
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:43,843
[Gavin] That’s wonderful, Auntie.

128
00:05:43,926 --> 00:05:45,762
[tense sinister music playing]

129
00:05:46,304 --> 00:05:47,513
[in English] I’m happy for you.

130
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:49,015
[in English] We’re so happy
for you, Audrey.

131
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:53,978
[in English] Congratulations, Audrey.

132
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:56,773
Hopefully, this makes up for everything.

133
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:00,610
[in English] I want to see her.

134
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:13,998
Just to clarify, all right? Uh…

135
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:16,292
You were about to leave the country

136
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:17,877
when your child was kidnapped?

137
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,046
By my ex-husband.

138
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:23,966
[in English] You see, Maxwell and I
just got married last month.

139
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:26,135
And you planned to take the child to…

140
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:27,512
[Maxwell] To Switzerland.

141
00:06:27,595 --> 00:06:29,430
That’s where my businesses are.

142
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:32,016
And that’s where Rita and I
will build our family.

143
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:34,644
[Rita, in English] Uh, I need to know.

144
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:37,188
Will you be able to find my child?

145
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,149
[in English] Yes, Mrs. Gastambide.

146
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:41,943
My tracker is excellent.

147
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:43,486
[in English] So, no need
to worry about that.

148
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:46,072
I just want all the facts.

149
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:50,618
Whatever you do to get my child back,

150
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:53,204
please make sure she won’t be traumatized.

151
00:06:53,287 --> 00:06:54,664
[in English] Of course.

152
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:56,249
Where is your tracker?

153
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,292
Shouldn’t he be here?

154
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:00,169
Will he understand all our instructions?

155
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:01,629
[in English] Don’t worry.

156
00:07:02,421 --> 00:07:06,717
He hears every word we’re saying.

157
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:09,428
I already gave the slip to teacher!

158
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:11,973
I’m excited for the field trip!

159
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:15,393
Janine, your mom really
didn’t allow you to go?

160
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:16,936
She didn’t!

161
00:07:17,019 --> 00:07:18,771
Why do you keep repeating it?

162
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,189
Are you teasing me?

163
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,275
We just want you to come with us!

164
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:23,526
And you’re the one who’s mad?

165
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:26,529
Yeah! I know! Let’s just go!

166
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:32,368
[melancholic music playing]

167
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:37,081
Don’t fight with them, Janine.

168
00:07:38,207 --> 00:07:41,043
Or your friends might leave you.

169
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,212
You stay away from me.

170
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:44,672
I’m fed up with you!

171
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:50,428
What you told me the other day was true.

172
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:51,888
I’m not really the child

173
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:55,391
of the man who pretended to be my father.

174
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:58,227
That’s why I understand you, Janine.

175
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:02,565
Because neither of us
knows our real parents.

176
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:05,109
We’re not the same,
because I don’t act like I’m smarter

177
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:06,903
than everyone else like you do!

178
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:26,339
Janine.

179
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:28,633
[music fades]

180
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:30,927
I’ve found your real mother.

181
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,596
I don’t understand.

182
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:40,770
[sentimental music playing]

183
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,032
Hello, Janine.

184
00:08:53,115 --> 00:08:57,161
[sobs]

185
00:09:02,124 --> 00:09:03,584
Oh! Big Sis Karla!

186
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:04,961
Ibyang, let’s go!

187
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:08,130
If you’re going to ask me
to buy something, I don’t have money.

188
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:10,508
Come on, big sis!

189
00:09:10,591 --> 00:09:13,010
Do you think I always
ask you to "buy me things"?

190
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:13,970
[smirks]

191
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:15,846
Come on. Let’s go home.

192
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:21,018
- [pensive music playing]
- [Karla sighs]

193
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:24,522
[titters]

194
00:09:24,605 --> 00:09:25,648
Wait.

195
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,109
I don’t understand.

196
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:31,946
Uh, it’s simple, Janine.

197
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:34,991
Ma’am Audrey is your real mother.

198
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:43,457
You?

199
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:48,004
You’re the ones
who gave me up for adoption?

200
00:09:50,548 --> 00:09:52,425
Why did you do this?

201
00:09:52,508 --> 00:09:53,634
[music fades]

202
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:56,429
I’m sorry, my child.

203
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:59,140
[somber music playing]

204
00:09:59,223 --> 00:10:01,642
I never wanted this to happen.

205
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:05,813
But let’s just think about

206
00:10:06,522 --> 00:10:09,025
the fact that I’m here now.

207
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:15,740
I never thought I’d see you again.

208
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:21,996
Let me make it up to you.

209
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:25,333
Now that we’re together. [sniffles]

210
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:28,294
Together?

211
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:33,341
I’ll go with you?

212
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:36,302
- [soft chuckle]
- You’ll take me away from…

213
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:38,512
from my mom?

214
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:40,806
[Martina clears throat]

215
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:43,184
No one’s forcing you, Janine.

216
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:46,062
Your real mother
just wants to be with you.

217
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:48,147
Maybe you should go to her house,

218
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:50,358
so you can talk properly.

219
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:53,361
[tense music playing]

220
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:58,199
[music concludes]

221
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:13,172
[Dmitri] So, Gavin, how are your studies?

222
00:11:13,255 --> 00:11:14,298
[Audrey] Dad…

223
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,092
Gavin…

224
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:19,136
[in English] This is Janine.

225
00:11:20,221 --> 00:11:23,849
Janine, this is your grandfather Dmitri.

226
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:27,228
And my nephew, your Big Brother Gavin.

227
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:28,687
Hello, Janine!

228
00:11:30,064 --> 00:11:32,942
[pensive music playing]

229
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:35,444
[Dmitri chuckles]

230
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:41,158
Welcome to your new home, my grandchild.

231
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:44,078
This will be my house?

232
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:45,996
Really?

233
00:11:48,457 --> 00:11:49,417
[music swells]

234
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,001
[Audrey, in English] Yes, Janine.

235
00:11:51,669 --> 00:11:52,503
[music fades]

236
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:54,672
Are you really my mother?

237
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:59,385
If it’s all right with you…

238
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:02,930
this will be your home.

239
00:12:03,013 --> 00:12:04,974
[pensive music playing]

240
00:12:05,057 --> 00:12:06,350
[Dmitri, in English] Very well then.

241
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:08,269
Say goodbye to your mother.

242
00:12:08,352 --> 00:12:09,645
[smirks]

243
00:12:09,728 --> 00:12:11,397
She doesn’t love me anyway.

244
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,065
That damn child.

245
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:17,153
After I raised you for eight years?!

246
00:12:17,236 --> 00:12:18,529
Ingrate!

247
00:12:18,612 --> 00:12:20,281
Let’s not blame each other.

248
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:21,699
[suspicious music playing]

249
00:12:21,782 --> 00:12:25,786
We’ll make sure you’re compensated

250
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,747
for all the years Janine
was under your care.

251
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:31,542
Don’t worry, Roma and I
already have an agreement.

252
00:12:33,752 --> 00:12:34,795
Come now.

253
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:36,839
[Martina clears throat]

254
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:37,840
[Roma] All right.

255
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,470
Welcome to your new home, my child.

256
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:43,596
[door clicks shut]

257
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:52,938
[music fades]

258
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:54,940
Look at this girl.

259
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:57,651
Just when the field trip is near,
she starts to get emotional!

260
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:04,033
I was just thinking about
my schoolmate, Janine.

261
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:05,117
‪[gentle music playing]

262
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:07,620
The one who bullied me.

263
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,371
The one who said I’m adopted.

264
00:13:09,455 --> 00:13:11,749
But she did that

265
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:14,418
because she’s an orphan too!

266
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:18,255
I tried to be her friend,

267
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:21,008
but she still picks on me!

268
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:24,970
If I were you, girl, I’ll ignore her!

269
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:26,722
You already did your part.

270
00:13:26,805 --> 00:13:28,891
What about the one bullying Ibyang?

271
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:31,435
Next time she bullies you…

272
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:33,771
don’t back down.

273
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:35,439
Fight back!

274
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:38,150
Don’t show her she can push you around.

275
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,069
- Or she’ll never stop!
- [quirky music playing]

276
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:41,779
[Ame] Shush, Karla!

277
00:13:41,862 --> 00:13:43,531
Don’t say that.

278
00:13:44,365 --> 00:13:45,783
[music concludes]

279
00:13:45,866 --> 00:13:47,117
Ibyang,

280
00:13:47,868 --> 00:13:51,205
you know those kids
from the orphanage, right?

281
00:13:51,747 --> 00:13:54,833
They all have their own trauma.

282
00:13:55,417 --> 00:13:56,710
So just try to understand them.

283
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:58,546
Stay away from them, okay?

284
00:13:58,629 --> 00:14:01,924
[gentle music playing]

285
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:03,384
[Cita] Ibyang!

286
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:06,554
Here’s your packed lunch
for tomorrow’s field trip.

287
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:07,930
[in English] Thank you.

288
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:10,057
Wait.

289
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,269
Where’s Master?

290
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:16,146
[light music playing]

291
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,815
[sighs]

292
00:14:23,028 --> 00:14:24,196
[woman] Hold on, don’t worry.

293
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:28,868
- [music fades]
- [man] Oh.

294
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,369
C’mon, sis.

295
00:14:31,036 --> 00:14:33,998
[suspicious music playing]

296
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:41,088
[soft rock music playing]

297
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:02,401
[soft rock music playing]

298
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,759
[line rings]

299
00:15:26,842 --> 00:15:28,177
Hello, sir.

300
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,887
[rock music playing]

301
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:31,472
I’ve located the father and child.

302
00:15:31,555 --> 00:15:34,308
As expected. Where did you see them?

303
00:15:34,391 --> 00:15:35,517
[in English] Well…

304
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:38,103
old habits die hard.

305
00:15:38,687 --> 00:15:42,316
They’re at their favorite hangout spot.

306
00:15:42,399 --> 00:15:44,318
Just a reminder.

307
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:47,154
This mission is delicate,

308
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:49,198
because a child is involved.

309
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:51,659
We can’t be reckless.

310
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:53,118
[in English] Copy, sir.

311
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:55,621
I’ll handle it.

312
00:15:55,704 --> 00:15:57,748
I’ll find out when the father leaves,

313
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:59,667
so I can find a window.

314
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,002
[in English] Keep me posted.

315
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:03,295
[in English] Yes, sir.

316
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:11,512
Wow!

317
00:16:11,595 --> 00:16:12,721
It’s huge!

318
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:16,600
This will be your room for now, my child.

319
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:20,521
My own room?

320
00:16:20,604 --> 00:16:22,898
Our whole house could fit in here.

321
00:16:28,737 --> 00:16:31,573
Uh, why did you give me up for adoption?

322
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,450
You were rich anyway.

323
00:16:34,034 --> 00:16:37,621
[somber music playing]

324
00:16:38,205 --> 00:16:39,581
Janine…

325
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:44,503
I never wanted that to happen.

326
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:50,259
I… was sick back then.

327
00:16:51,927 --> 00:16:53,303
Then suddenly…

328
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:56,807
someone took you.

329
00:16:57,516 --> 00:16:59,309
[tense sting]

330
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:01,020
I only found out later…

331
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:04,690
you’d already been adopted.

332
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:07,317
[Janine] That’s awful.

333
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:09,486
I should’ve been rich all along.

334
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:12,281
Um, Janine,

335
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:14,199
don’t think about things like that.

336
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:17,119
What matters now is that
you’re with your mommy.

337
00:17:17,202 --> 00:17:18,579
[sighs]

338
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:19,747
Uh,

339
00:17:20,497 --> 00:17:22,583
can I call you Mommy?

340
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:27,004
[gentle music playing]

341
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:28,297
[in English] Yes.

342
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,050
Yes, my child.

343
00:17:33,635 --> 00:17:35,888
Um, dear?

344
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,432
[in English] Yes, Mommy?

345
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:42,144
So, what do you want to do tomorrow?

346
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:46,774
Do you want to go shopping
for new clothes?

347
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,359
Sure, I’d love that.

348
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:52,112
Oh, but we have a field trip tomorrow.

349
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:53,655
Let’s go there instead.

350
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:56,492
Ah, well, of course.

351
00:17:56,575 --> 00:17:58,118
[in English] Whatever you want.

352
00:17:58,202 --> 00:17:59,495
[Dmitri] Uh, but, Audrey…

353
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:01,705
[in English] Are you sure
you’re okay with that?

354
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:03,874
You just had surgery.

355
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:06,168
[in English] I’m fine.

356
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:09,421
Okay, then.

357
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:11,465
I’ll come with you. Just to be sure.

358
00:18:11,548 --> 00:18:13,509
[in English] I said I’m fine… Dad.

359
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:15,219
I’ll go with you, Auntie.

360
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:19,181
That would be good, Gavin.

361
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:23,185
[sentimental music playing]

362
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,829
[music fades]

363
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:47,084
Oh? What’s your problem?

364
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:48,001
[sighs]

365
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:50,546
I’m upset with Master!

366
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:54,633
He said he won’t come with me
to the field trip tomorrow!

367
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:57,970
It’s written on my permission slip

368
00:18:58,053 --> 00:19:00,347
that my father will be with me.

369
00:19:01,014 --> 00:19:04,101
- Maybe he has an important mission.
- [Ibyang sighs]

370
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:07,020
And you’ll have plenty
of company anyway, right?

371
00:19:07,104 --> 00:19:08,438
[somber music playing]

372
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:11,441
But Big Sis Ame, he promised!

373
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:14,862
And he’s the one I really want to be with!

374
00:19:15,779 --> 00:19:18,365
Master’s so confusing.

375
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:24,371
He said he’d be my dad,
but it doesn’t feel like it.

376
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,168
[sighs]

377
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:35,716
[music fades]

378
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:41,805
Wow! Beautiful!

379
00:19:41,889 --> 00:19:43,265
Do you like your new outfit, dear?

380
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:45,601
[Janine] Yes, Mommy. It’s gorgeous.

381
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:47,603
It even looks good on you.

382
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:50,606
My child…

383
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:51,773
[in English] Yes, Mommy?

384
00:19:52,816 --> 00:19:54,651
I know…

385
00:19:55,736 --> 00:19:59,364
this is a huge change in your life.

386
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:00,741
[sighs]

387
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:02,701
But it’s fun.

388
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:03,702
[chuckles softly]

389
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:05,913
[in English] I’m so glad
you feel that way.

390
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:11,043
I promised you
I’d make it up to you, right?

391
00:20:12,127 --> 00:20:13,670
Part of that is…

392
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:18,800
I want to transfer you
to a good private school.

393
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:20,928
Ah, maybe next school year.

394
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:22,763
I don’t want to, Mommy.

395
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:25,557
Why not, my child?

396
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:29,353
Because my friends are at my school.

397
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:32,522
Ah, okay…

398
00:20:32,606 --> 00:20:35,150
Fine, if that’s what you want.

399
00:20:35,734 --> 00:20:36,818
[in English] Let’s go?

400
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:39,571
We’ll go ahead.

401
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:41,657
[Gavin] Bye.

402
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,283
- Bye!
- [in English] Let’s go!

403
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:44,201
[Gavin, in English] Let’s go.

404
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:45,452
Mom, Dad.

405
00:20:45,535 --> 00:20:47,287
[Red] Okay. Take care.

406
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:52,542
[door clicks shut]

407
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:55,045
[in English] I honestly can’t believe
how gullible your sister is.

408
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:58,507
[in English] All we had to do was forge
the DNA test and voila!

409
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:00,175
She has a child now!

410
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:03,178
In fairness, your plan was genius.

411
00:21:03,971 --> 00:21:06,598
Surely Dad will forgive us now, right?

412
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:08,016
[Martina, in English] Why not?

413
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,518
[in English] This is all
that he wanted, right?

414
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:12,354
Why didn’t we think of this earlier?

415
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:14,731
We even searched for the real child,

416
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,692
and I got sore from that convent trip.

417
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:19,403
[in English] This is
so much better, though, isn’t it?

418
00:21:19,486 --> 00:21:21,822
I love it when your sister
looks like a fool.

419
00:21:21,905 --> 00:21:24,574
That’s my revenge for her
being such a bitch in our lives.

420
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:25,993
[cackles]

421
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:28,120
[tense music playing]

422
00:21:36,878 --> 00:21:43,343
[soft rock music playing]

423
00:22:03,113 --> 00:22:06,241
[pleasant music playing]

424
00:22:06,950 --> 00:22:08,910
[teacher] Class, aside from the rides,

425
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:12,247
we also have games
you can play with your parents.

426
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:14,249
But let’s all be careful, okay?

427
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:16,585
Parents, please watch over your children.

428
00:22:16,668 --> 00:22:18,462
- Don’t leave them alone.
- [kids murmur]

429
00:22:18,545 --> 00:22:20,422
[in English] Enjoy, everybody!

430
00:22:20,505 --> 00:22:21,965
[in English] Enjoy!

431
00:22:22,049 --> 00:22:23,133
[lively chattering]

432
00:22:23,216 --> 00:22:24,593
So, Ibyang…

433
00:22:25,218 --> 00:22:26,386
where do you want to go?

434
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:27,387
[Tonet] I know what to do!

435
00:22:27,471 --> 00:22:30,015
Let’s head to the games Teacher mentioned.

436
00:22:30,098 --> 00:22:32,476
[Karla] Yes! I’m good at those.

437
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:34,019
I grew up going to the fair!

438
00:22:34,102 --> 00:22:35,187
[Tonet] Oh, that’s perfect!

439
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,564
Ibyang will take home
lots of stuffed toys.

440
00:22:37,647 --> 00:22:38,482
Ibyang!

441
00:22:38,565 --> 00:22:40,025
- I’ll handle it.
- Ibyang!

442
00:22:40,108 --> 00:22:41,610
Hey, brother!

443
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:43,820
[elated shriek]

444
00:22:44,404 --> 00:22:45,739
[Tonet] Why are you here?

445
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:47,866
Atoy asked me to help.

446
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:50,452
I’m standing in as Ibyang’s dad.

447
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:53,038
Oh? And Sis Ame is the mom?

448
00:22:53,121 --> 00:22:53,955
- [quirky sting]
- Mmm.

449
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:54,956
Too bad.

450
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:57,042
From Atoy to Emerson.

451
00:22:57,125 --> 00:22:58,001
What a downgrade!

452
00:22:58,085 --> 00:23:00,003
- Wow, you’re so mean to me, Ame.
- [Tonet chuckles]

453
00:23:00,087 --> 00:23:01,129
Actually, you two look good together!

454
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:03,882
- Oh, this looks like a nice love team.
- [Karla chuckles]

455
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:04,925
Actually, we’re late.

456
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:06,259
The stuffed toys are almost gone.

457
00:23:06,343 --> 00:23:07,677
- Come on! Stand here…
- [Emerson] Okay.

458
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:08,762
- So, they can hold hands.
- [Ame moans]

459
00:23:08,845 --> 00:23:11,264
[Karla] Hold hands now. There you go!

460
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:13,266
See? You look good together.

461
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,227
Wow! Let me help you.

462
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:17,270
- Oh!
- [Tonet giggles]

463
00:23:17,354 --> 00:23:19,356
- [Karla] My sis!
- [Tonet] Are you lost?

464
00:23:19,439 --> 00:23:23,777
[pleasant music playing]

465
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:30,826
[music fades]

466
00:23:31,409 --> 00:23:35,080
[pensive music playing]

467
00:23:36,414 --> 00:23:38,125
Ahh! I’m so excited!

468
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:39,584
[chuckles]

469
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:43,171
Let me see first.

470
00:23:43,255 --> 00:23:44,589
Ah, it’s so beautiful.

471
00:23:44,673 --> 00:23:46,591
[suspicious music playing]

472
00:24:09,072 --> 00:24:10,115
[Audrey exclaims]

473
00:24:10,198 --> 00:24:12,033
[in English] Let’s go!

474
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:17,038
[tense music playing]

475
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:18,415
[in English] Have you seen my phone?

476
00:24:18,498 --> 00:24:20,125
Weren’t you holding it earlier?

477
00:24:22,919 --> 00:24:24,504
- [in English] Ah, I found it.
- [Gavin mutters]

478
00:24:26,715 --> 00:24:30,385
[electronic blipping]

479
00:24:33,013 --> 00:24:36,391
[tense music playing]

480
00:24:36,474 --> 00:24:37,309
Update?

481
00:24:37,392 --> 00:24:39,019
I’m here at the theme park.

482
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:42,355
It’s fine, there’s a lot of people here.
It will be easy to intercept.

483
00:24:42,439 --> 00:24:44,316
[Janine] <i>I saw my real mommy.</i>

484
00:24:44,399 --> 00:24:47,402
She’s beautiful like me,
and she bought me a lovely dress.

485
00:24:47,485 --> 00:24:49,696
You? Where’s your fake dad?

486
00:24:49,779 --> 00:24:50,697
UP NEXT

487
00:24:53,825 --> 00:24:55,327
- [screams and gasps]
- [squeals]

488
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:57,162
[growls]

489
00:24:57,245 --> 00:24:58,663
[Sabrina] Dad!

490
00:24:58,747 --> 00:25:00,248
[Noel grunts] Sabrina!

491
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:02,250
[Sabrina] I don’t want you!

492
00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:03,668
- I don’t want you!
- Shh!

493
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:05,212
- I won’t hurt you!
- I don’t want you!

494
00:25:05,295 --> 00:25:06,588
Don’t worry, I’ll bring you back
to your mother!

495
00:25:06,671 --> 00:25:09,299
- I don’t want you!
- Don’t worry, I won’t hurt you.

496
00:25:09,382 --> 00:25:10,342
I don’t want you--

497
00:25:10,425 --> 00:25:12,427
I’ll kill you first
before you can do that!

498
00:25:12,510 --> 00:25:14,930
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

499
00:25:18,808 --> 00:25:22,229
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
